Description: Rim and body sherd of Aeolian Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; cream slip; interior: glazed streaky black; exterior: on top of rim, guilloche; outside of rim glazed; reserved band at top of shoulder above hook maeander frize between lines; below, alternating red and black tongues between pairs of verticals.
Producer name: Attributed to: The London Dinos Group
Curator's comments: Very close to a fragment of dinos rim from Berezan, Posamentir and Solovyoy, Ist.Mitt. 56 (2006) 106, fig. 2, 2 and 57 (2007) 190 and fig. 3, 13.
Bibliographic references: Lemos 1991 / Archaic Pottery of Chios. The Decorated Styles (p. 246, no. 292)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.03)
